	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">ulfalizer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Ah, I see what's going on in sync_dmc_fast now. The first write to $4015 immediately loads the final sample byte (since there's only one and the DPCM is drained). The second write to $4015 then starts a new sample before the old one has finished, meaning its final sample byte will be loaded at the next DMC clock after the old sample finishes. That makes it possible to sync on the DMC clock.</div><br />And I believe the third write is in case the sample just began playing after the second write (which would generate an immediate IRQ). The third would ensure that another one is reliably pending after the operation. I'm pretty sure I added the third write after I got two to fail at the desired task on hardware.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


